Tallahassee and Leon County are home to Florida State University, Florida A&M University, Tallahassee Community College and several trade schools with a student population of more than 65,000. Tallahassee as the State Capital brings visitors from around the state as well as the country. Families make up 65% of the households in Leon County. This figure includes both married-couple families (44 %) and other families (21 %). The median income of households in Leon County in 2012 was $39,649. About Oak View Group (OVG) Oak View Group (OVG) is the global leader in live experience venue development, management, premium hospitality services, and 360-degree solutions for a collection of world-class owned venues and a client roster of arenas, convention centers, music festivals, performing arts centers, and cultural institutions. Founded by Tim Leiweke and Irving Azoff in 2015, OVG is the leading developer of major new venues either open or under development across four continents.
